{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846140081,"sessionID":"ses_28753027dffeVp68suk2dqdsjB","part":{"id":"prt_d78ada14b001o4rPBX7R78xoov","messageID":"msg_d78ad98d10011JAuzTnuRUdSpl","sessionID":"ses_28753027dffeVp68suk2dqdsjB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_908a3936805d4685af31b875","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/idle-cleanup/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/idle-cleanup/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Idle Cleanup — Design\n2: \n3: ## Module\n4: \n5: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` (see root `go.mod` in sandbox-orchestration design).\n6: \n7: ## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd`\n8: \n9: ### Time threshold\n10: \n11: ```go\n12: var SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n13: ```\n14: \n15: Idle expiration: `expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`; delete when `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`.\n16: \n17: ### Annotation key\n18: \n19: The reconciler uses the same key as workload manager pod annotation for idle timeout tracking on the **Sandbox** object:\n20: \n21: - Import: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager`\n22: - Key: `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey` = **`\"last-activity-time\"`**\n23: \n24: (Workload manager also sets `runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout` on Sandbox metadata for template-driven idle configuration; **agentd** only reads `last-activity-time`.)\n25: \n26: ### Reconciler\n27: \n28: ```go\n29: package agentd\n30: \n31: type Reconciler struct {\n32:     client.Client\n33:     Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n34: }\n35: \n36: func (r *Reconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error)\n37: ```\n38: \n39: **Algorithm (exact behavior):**\n40: \n41: 1. `sandbox := &sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}`; `Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, sandbox)`.\n42: 2. If `errors.IsNotFound(err)` → `return ctrl.Result{}, nil`.\n43: 3. If other get error → return `ctrl.Result{}, err`.\n44: 4. `lastActivityStr, exists := sandbox.Annotations[workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey]`.\n45: 5. If `exists && lastActivityStr != \"\"`:\n46:    - `lastActivity, err := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, lastActivityStr)`\n47:    - If parse err → `return ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: 30 * time.Second}, err`\n48:    - `expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`\n49:    - If `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`:\n50:      - `r.Delete(ctx, sandbox)`; if err and not `IsNotFound` → `return ctrl.Result{}, err`\n51:    - Else:\n52:      - `return ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)}, nil`\n53: 6. `return ctrl.Result{}, nil`\n54: \n55: ### SetupWithManager\n56: \n57: ```go\n58: func (r *Reconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error {\n59:     return ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n60:         For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}).\n61:         Complete(r)\n62: }\n63: ```\n64: \n65: ## Binary `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n66: \n67: ### Scheme registration\n68: \n69: ```go\n70: var schemeBuilder = runtime.NewScheme()\n71: \n72: func init() {\n73:     utilruntime.Must(scheme.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n74:     utilruntime.Must(sandboxv1alpha1.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n75: }\n76: ```\n77: \n78: ### Controller-runtime manager\n79: \n80: ```go\n81: mgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(ctrl.GetConfigOrDie(), ctrl.Options{\n82:     Scheme:                 schemeBuilder,\n83:     Metrics:                metricsserver.Options{BindAddress: \"0\"},\n84:     HealthProbeBindAddress:   \"0\",\n85: })\n86: ```\n87: \n88: ### Controller registration (duplicate of SetupWithManager pattern)\n89: \n90: ```go\n91: err = ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n92:     For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}).\n93:     Complete(&agentd.Reconciler{\n94:         Client: mgr.GetClient(),\n95:         Scheme: mgr.GetScheme(),\n96:     })\n97: ```\n98: \n99: ### Run\n100: \n101: ```go\n102: mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())\n103: ```\n104: \n105: ## Watched resources\n106: \n107: | API group | Version | Kind | Trigger |\n108: |-----------|---------|------|---------|\n109: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `v1alpha1` | `Sandbox` | Default `For()` watch — creates, updates, deletes (per controller-runtime) |\n110: \n111: No explicit `Owns` or `Watches` — single primary resource `Sandbox`.\n112: \n113: ## Related workload-manager constants (context)\n114: \n115: From `pkg/workloadmanager` (not used by agentd reconcile logic but set when sandboxes are created):\n116: \n117: - `IdleTimeoutAnnotationKey = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"` — duration string on Sandbox CR.\n118: - `LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"last-activity-time\"` — **read by agentd** for idle cleanup.\n119: \n120: ## Dependencies\n121: \n122: - `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors`\n123: - `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime`\n124: - `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1`\n125: - `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime`\n126: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` (annotation key only)\n\n(End of file - total 126 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Idle Cleanup — Design\n\n## Module\n\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` (see root `go.mod` in sandbox-orchestration design).\n\n## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd`\n\n### Time threshold\n\n```go\nvar SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n```\n\nIdle expiration: `expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`; delete when `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`.\n\n### Annotation key\n\nThe reconciler uses the same key as workload manager pod annotation for idle timeout tracking on the **Sandbox** object:\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/idle-cleanup/design.md","time":{"start":1775846140070,"end":1775846140079}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846140092,"sessionID":"ses_28753027dffeVp68suk2dqdsjB","part":{"id":"prt_d78ada529001NP4CZghLcePMR0","messageID":"msg_d78ad98d10011JAuzTnuRUdSpl","sessionID":"ses_28753027dffeVp68suk2dqdsjB","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_1bd03bcd47774d428dd0b2d3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-006: Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 (Sandbox Deletion and Lifecycle Management)\n2: \n3: - **AR ID**: AR-006\n4: - **Module**: pkg/workloadmanager\n5: - **Language**: Go\n6: - **Size**: M\n7: - **Status**: ST-1 Completed\n8: \n9: ## 1. Architecture\n10: \n11: ### 1.1 Overview\n12: \n13: The Sandbox Lifecycle Management feature extends the WorkloadManager module to provide comprehensive deletion and lifecycle management for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources. This includes graceful termination, finalizer-based cleanup, deletion callbacks, and lifecycle hooks.\n14: \n15: ### 1.2 Component Structure\n16: \n17: ```\n18: pkg/workloadmanager/\n19: ├── client.go              # Kubernetes client initialization (existing)\n20: ├── service.go             # WorkloadManager interface (existing)\n21: ├── server.go              # HTTP server (existing)\n22: ├── types.go               # Request/Response types (existing)\n23: ├── lifecycle.go           # NEW: Lifecycle management interface\n24: ├── deletion.go            # NEW: Deletion operations\n25: ├── cleanup.go             # NEW: Cleanup handlers\n26: ├── finalizer.go           # NEW: Finalizer management\n27: ├── events.go              # NEW: Lifecycle event recording\n28: └── design.md              # This design document\n29: ```\n30: \n31: ### 1.3 Layered Architecture\n32: \n33: ```\n34: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n35: │           HTTP API Layer                │\n36: │         (server.go + deletion)          │\n37: ├─────────────────────────────────────────┤\n38: │        Lifecycle Management             │\n39: │    (lifecycle.go + finalizer.go)        │\n40: ├─────────────────────────────────────────┤\n41: │         Service Layer                   │\n42: │      (WorkloadManager interface)        │\n43: ├─────────────────────────────────────────┤\n44: │         Client Layer                    │\n45: │     (versioned.Interface wrapper)       │\n46: ├─────────────────────────────────────────┤\n47: │       Generated client-go               │\n48: │   github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go │\n49: └─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n50: ```\n51: \n52: ## 2. Data Structures\n53: \n54: ### 2.1 Core Types\n55: \n56: #### LifecycleManager Interface\n57: \n58: ```go\n59: type LifecycleManager interface {\n60:     // Deletion operations\n61:     DeleteAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string, opts DeletionOptions) error\n62:     DeleteCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string, opts DeletionOptions) error\n63:     \n64:     // Force deletion (skip cleanup)\n65:     ForceDeleteAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) error\n66:     ForceDeleteCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) error\n67:     \n68:     // Lifecycle hooks\n69:     RegisterDeletionHook(hook DeletionHook) error\n70:     UnregisterDeletionHook(hookID string) error\n71:     \n72:     // Status queries\n73:     GetDeletionStatus(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string, resourceType ResourceType) (*DeletionStatus, error)\n74:     \n75:     // Cleanup operations\n76:     CleanupOrphanedResources(ctx context.Context, namespace string) (*CleanupReport, error)\n77:     \n78:     Close() error\n79: }\n80: ```\n81: \n82: #### DeletionOptions\n83: \n84: ```go\n85: type DeletionOptions struct {\n86:     // GracePeriodSeconds is the duration to wait before deleting the resource\n87:     GracePeriodSeconds *int64 `json:\"gracePeriodSeconds,omitempty\"`\n88:     \n89:     // PreDeleteHook is an optional callback invoked before deletion\n90:     PreDeleteHook string `json:\"preDeleteHook,omitempty\"`\n91:     \n92:     // SkipFinalizers forces immediate deletion, bypassing finalizers\n93:     SkipFinalizers bool `json:\"skipFinalizers,omitempty\"`\n94:     \n95:     // DeletePods also deletes associated pods\n96:     DeletePods bool `json:\"deletePods,omitempty\"`\n97:     \n98:     // DeletePVCs deletes associated persistent volume claims\n99:     DeletePVCs bool `json:\"deletePVCs,omitempty\"`\n100:     \n101:     // PropagationPolicy defines the deletion policy\n102:     PropagationPolicy DeletePropagationPolicy `json:\"propagationPolicy,omitempty\"`\n103: }\n104: ```\n105: \n106: #### DeletePropagationPolicy\n107: \n108: ```go\n109: type DeletePropagationPolicy string\n110: \n111: const (\n112:     // DeletePropagationOrphan - leaves orphaned resources\n113:     DeletePropagationOrphan DeletePropagationPolicy = \"Orphan\"\n114:     // DeletePropagationBackground - deletes in background\n115:     DeletePropagationBackground DeletePropagationPolicy = \"Background\"\n116:     // DeletePropagationForeground - deletes in foreground\n117:     DeletePropagationForeground DeletePropagationPolicy = \"Foreground\"\n118: )\n119: ```\n120: \n121: #### DeletionHook\n122: \n123: ```go\n124: type DeletionHook interface {\n125:     ID() string\n126:     Priority() int\n127:     PreDelete(ctx context.Context, resource ResourceRef) error\n128:     PostDelete(ctx context.Context, resource ResourceRef, result DeleteResult) error\n129: }\n130: \n131: type ResourceRef struct {\n132:     Type       ResourceType\n133:     Namespace  string\n134:     Name       string\n135:     UID        types.UID\n136:     Generation int64\n137: }\n138: \n139: type DeleteResult struct {\n140:     Success    bool\n141:     Error      error\n142:     Duration   time.Duration\n143:     Resources  []DeletedResource\n144: }\n145: \n146: type DeletedResource struct {\n147:     Kind       string\n148:     Namespace  string\n149:     Name       string\n150:     UID        types.UID\n151: }\n152: ```\n153: \n154: #### DeletionStatus\n155: \n156: ```go\n157: type DeletionStatus struct {\n158:     Phase              DeletionPhase\n159:     StartTime          *metav1.Time\n160:     CompletionTime     *metav1.Time\n161:     ActiveFinalizers   []string\n162:     PendingOperations  []PendingOperation\n163:     OrphanedResources  []OrphanedResource\n164:     Conditions         []metav1.Condition\n165: }\n166: \n167: type DeletionPhase string\n168: \n169: const (\n170:     DeletionPhasePending    DeletionPhase = \"Pending\"\n171:     DeletionPhasePreDelete  DeletionPhase = \"PreDelete\"\n172:     DeletionPhaseDeleting   DeletionPhase = \"Deleting\"\n173:     DeletionPhaseFinalizing DeletionPhase = \"Finalizing\"\n174:     DeletionPhaseCompleted  DeletionPhase = \"Completed\"\n175:     DeletionPhaseFailed     DeletionPhase = \"Failed\"\n176: )\n177: \n178: type PendingOperation struct {\n179:     ID        string\n180:     Type      string\n181:     StartedAt *metav1.Time\n182: }\n183: \n184: type OrphanedResource struct {\n185:     Kind      string\n186:     Namespace string\n187:     Name      string\n188:     UID       types.UID\n189: }\n190: ```\n191: \n192: #### CleanupReport\n193: \n194: ```go\n195: type CleanupReport struct {\n196:     StartTime       metav1.Time\n197:     EndTime         metav1.Time\n198:     TotalScanned    int\n199:     TotalCleaned    int\n200:     TotalFailed     int\n201:     CleanedResources []DeletedResource\n202:     FailedResources  []FailedResource\n203: }\n204: \n205: type FailedResource struct {\n206:     Kind      string\n207:     Namespace string\n208:     Name      string\n209:     Error     string\n210: }\n211: ```\n212: \n213: ### 2.2 Request/Response Types\n214: \n215: | Type | File | Purpose |\n216: |------|------|---------|\n217: | DeleteAgentRuntimeRequest | lifecycle.go | AgentRuntime deletion request |\n218: | DeleteCodeInterpreterRequest | lifecycle.go | CodeInterpreter deletion request |\n219: | DeleteResponse | lifecycle.go | Standard deletion response |\n220: | DeletionStatusResponse | lifecycle.go | Deletion status query response |\n221: | CleanupRequest | cleanup.go | Cleanup operation request |\n222: | CleanupResponse | cleanup.go | Cleanup operation result |\n223: \n224: ### 2.3 API Types Extension\n225: \n226: Extend `AgentRuntimeStatus` and `CodeInterpreterStatus` with lifecycle fields:\n227: \n228: ```go\n229: // In pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go\n230: \n231: type AgentRuntimeStatus struct {\n232:     // ... existing fields ...\n233:     \n234:     // DeletionStatus holds the current deletion state\n235:     // +optional\n236:     DeletionStatus *DeletionStatus `json:\"deletionStatus,omitempty\"`\n237: }\n238: \n239: type CodeInterpreterStatus struct {\n240:     // ... existing fields ...\n241:     \n242:     // DeletionStatus holds the current deletion state\n243:     // +optional\n244:     DeletionStatus *DeletionStatus `json:\"deletionStatus,omitempty\"`\n245: }\n246: ```\n247: \n248: ## 3. API Contracts\n249: \n250: ### 3.1 New Endpoints\n251: \n252: | Operation | Method | Resource Path | Description |\n253: |-----------|--------|---------------|-------------|\n254: | Delete AgentRuntime | DELETE | /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name} | Graceful deletion with options |\n255: | Delete CodeInterpreter | DELETE | /apis/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name} | Graceful deletion with options |\n256: | Force Delete | POST | /apis/.../agentruntimes/{name}/force | Immediate deletion bypassing finalizers |\n257: | Deletion Status | GET | /apis/.../agentruntimes/{name}/deletionStatus | Get deletion progress |\n258: | Cleanup Orphans | POST | /apis/.../namespaces/{namespace}/cleanup | Clean orphaned resources |\n259: \n260: ### 3.2 Delete Request Parameters\n261: \n262: | Parameter | Type | Description |\n263: |-----------|------|-------------|\n264: | gracePeriodSeconds | int64 | Wait time before deletion |\n265: | skipFinalizers | bool | Force immediate deletion |\n266: | propagationPolicy | string | Orphan/Background/Foreground |\n267: | deletePods | bool | Also delete pods |\n268: | deletePVCs | bool | Also delete PVCs |\n269: | preDeleteHook | string | Hook identifier to execute |\n270: \n271: ### 3.3 Webhook Integration\n272: \n273: Support for pre-delete webhooks:\n274: \n275: ```yaml\n276: apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n277: kind: AgentRuntime\n278: metadata:\n279:   name: my-runtime\n280:   annotations:\n281:     agentcube.volcano.sh/pre-delete-hook: \"cleanup-script\"\n282: spec:\n283:   # ...\n284: ```\n285: \n286: ## 4. Error Handling\n287: \n288: ### 4.1 Error Types\n289: \n290: | Error Code | Reason | Description |\n291: |------------|--------|-------------|\n292: | 400 | BadRequest | Invalid deletion options |\n293: | 404 | NotFound | Resource not found |\n294: | 409 | Conflict | Resource already being deleted |\n295: | 422 | Invalid | Resource has invalid finalizer state |\n296: | 423 | Locked | Resource deletion is blocked |\n297: | 500 | InternalError | Deletion failed |\n298: | 503 | ServiceUnavailable | Cleanup service unavailable |\n299: \n300: ### 4.2 Deletion-Specific Errors\n301: \n302: ```go\n303: var (\n304:     ErrResourceNotFound        = errors.New(\"resource not found\")\n305:     ErrResourceAlreadyDeleted  = errors.New(\"resource is already being deleted\")\n306:     ErrDeletionBlocked         = errors.New(\"deletion blocked by finalizer\")\n307:     ErrDeletionTimeout         = errors.New(\"deletion timed out\")\n308:     ErrHookExecutionFailed     = errors.New(\"deletion hook execution failed\")\n309:     ErrOrphanedResourcesExist  = errors.New(\"orphaned resources exist\")\n310:     ErrCleanupFailed           = errors.New(\"cleanup operation failed\")\n311: )\n312: ```\n313: \n314: ### 4.3 Error Response Format\n315: \n316: ```json\n317: {\n318:   \"kind\": \"Status\",\n319:   \"apiVersion\": \"v1\",\n320:   \"status\": \"Failure\",\n321:   \"message\": \"deletion of AgentRuntime 'my-runtime' blocked by finalizer 'custom-finalizer'\",\n322:   \"reason\": \"DeletionBlocked\",\n323:   \"code\": 423,\n324:   \"details\": {\n325:     \"name\": \"my-runtime\",\n326:     \"kind\": \"agentruntime\",\n327:     \"blockedBy\": [\"custom-finalizer\"]\n328:   }\n329: }\n330: ```\n331: \n332: ## 5. Lifecycle Flows\n333: \n334: ### 5.1 Graceful Deletion Flow\n335: \n336: ```\n337: 1. Client sends DELETE request with DeletionOptions\n338: 2. Validate deletion options\n339: 3. Add/verify deletion finalizer\n340: 4. Set DeletionTimestamp\n341: 5. Execute PreDelete hooks (if configured)\n342: 6. Update status to Deleting\n343: 7. Delete dependent resources (pods, PVCs) based on options\n344: 8. Execute finalizers in order\n345: 9. Remove finalizers\n346: 10. Delete the resource from etcd\n347: 11. Execute PostDelete hooks\n348: 12. Record deletion event\n349: ```\n350: \n351: ### 5.2 Finalizer Management\n352: \n353: ```go\n354: const (\n355:     // FinalizerAgentRuntime is the standard finalizer for AgentRuntime\n356:     FinalizerAgentRuntime = \"agentruntime.agentcube.volcano.sh/deletion-protection\"\n357:     \n358:     // FinalizerCodeInterpreter is the standard finalizer for CodeInterpreter\n359:     FinalizerCodeInterpreter = \"codeinterpreter.agentcube.volcano.sh/deletion-protection\"\n360: )\n361: \n362: // AddFinalizer adds a finalizer to the resource\n363: func AddFinalizer(ctx context.Context, client versioned.Interface, resourceType ResourceType, namespace, name string, finalizer string) error\n364: \n365: // RemoveFinalizer removes a finalizer from the resource\n366: func RemoveFinalizer(ctx context.Context, client versioned.Interface, resourceType ResourceType, namespace, name string, finalizer string) error\n367: \n368: // HasFinalizer checks if resource has a specific finalizer\n369: func HasFinalizer(obj metav1.Object, finalizer string) bool\n370: ```\n371: \n372: ### 5.3 Cleanup Operations\n373: \n374: ```go\n375: type CleanupManager interface {\n376:     // Find orphaned resources in a namespace\n377:     FindOrphanedResources(ctx context.Context, namespace string) ([]OrphanedResource, error)\n378:     \n379:     // Delete orphaned resources\n380:     DeleteOrphanedResources(ctx context.Context, resources []OrphanedResource) (*CleanupReport, error)\n381:     \n382:     // Periodic cleanup task\n383:     StartCleanupWorker(stopCh <-chan struct{})\n384: }\n385: ```\n386: \n387: ## 6. Testing Strategy\n388: \n389: ### 6.1 Unit Tests\n390: \n391: #### Deletion Tests\n392: - Test graceful deletion with all options\n393: - Test force deletion bypassing finalizers\n394: - Test deletion with propagation policies\n395: - Test finalizer add/remove operations\n396: \n397: #### Hook Tests\n398: - Test hook registration/unregistration\n399: - Test hook execution order by priority\n400: - Test hook timeout handling\n401: - Test hook error propagation\n402: \n403: #### Cleanup Tests\n404: - Test orphaned resource detection\n405: - Test cleanup with partial failures\n406: - Test cleanup idempotency\n407: \n408: ### 6.2 Integration Tests\n409: \n410: ```go\n411: func TestLifecycleIntegration(t *testing.T) {\n412:     // Test full deletion lifecycle\n413:     // 1. Create resource\n414:     // 2. Add custom finalizer\n415:     // 3. Initiate deletion\n416:     // 4. Verify status transitions\n417:     // 5. Remove finalizer\n418:     // 6. Verify resource deleted\n419: }\n420: ```\n421: \n422: ### 6.3 Test Coverage Targets\n423: \n424: | Component | Target Coverage |\n425: |-----------|-----------------|\n426: | lifecycle.go | 85% |\n427: | deletion.go | 85% |\n428: | cleanup.go | 80% |\n429: | finalizer.go | 90% |\n430: | events.go | 75% |\n431: \n432: ## 7. Dependencies\n433: \n434: ### 7.1 New Dependencies\n435: \n436: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n437: |---------|---------|---------|\n438: | k8s.io/client-go | latest | Kubernetes client (existing) |\n439: | k8s.io/apimachinery | latest | API types (existing) |\n440: | k8s.io/klog/v2 | latest | Logging (existing) |\n441: \n442: ### 7.2 Internal Dependencies\n443: \n444: | Module | Purpose |\n445: |--------|---------|\n446: | github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go | Generated client library |\n447: | github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1 | API types |\n448: \n449: ## 8. Configuration\n450: \n451: ### 8.1 Environment Variables\n452: \n453: | Variable | Default | Description |\n454: |----------|---------|-------------|\n455: | DEFAULT_GRACE_PERIOD | 30 | Default grace period in seconds |\n456: | MAX_GRACE_PERIOD | 3600 | Maximum grace period allowed |\n457: | CLEANUP_INTERVAL | 300 | Orphan cleanup interval in seconds |\n458: | HOOK_TIMEOUT | 60 | Deletion hook timeout in seconds |\n459: | FINALIZER_ENABLED | true | Enable default finalizers |\n460: \n461: ### 8.2 Flags\n462: \n463: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n464: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n465: | enable-finalizer | bool | true | Enable deletion finalizers |\n466: | grace-period | int | 30 | Default grace period |\n467: | cleanup-workers | int | 3 | Number of cleanup workers |\n468: \n469: ## 9. Security\n470: \n471: ### 9.1 RBAC Requirements\n472: \n473: ```yaml\n474: rules:\n475: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n476:   resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"codeinterpreters\"]\n477:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n478: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n479:   resources: [\"pods\", \"persistentvolumeclaims\"]\n480:   verbs: [\"delete\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n481: - apiGroups: [\"events.k8s.io\"]\n482:   resources: [\"events\"]\n483:   verbs: [\"create\", \"patch\"]\n484: ```\n485: \n486: ### 9.2 Finalizer Security\n487: \n488: - Default finalizers cannot be removed without proper authorization\n489: - Custom finalizer addition requires explicit permission\n490: - Hook execution runs with limited privileges\n491: \n492: ## 10. Monitoring\n493: \n494: ### 10.1 Metrics\n495: \n496: | Metric | Type | Description |\n497: |--------|------|-------------|\n498: | deletion_duration_seconds | Histogram | Deletion operation duration |\n499: | deletion_total | Counter | Total deletion operations |\n500: | deletion_failed_total | Counter | Failed deletion operations |\n501: | cleanup_orphaned_total | Counter | Orphaned resources cleaned up |\n502: | finalizer_removal_duration_seconds | Histogram | Finalizer removal time |\n503: \n504: ### 10.2 Events\n505: \n506: - `DeletionStarted` - Deletion initiated\n507: - `DeletionCompleted` - Deletion finished successfully\n508: - `DeletionFailed` - Deletion failed\n509: - `OrphanedResourcesFound` - Orphaned resources detected\n510: - `CleanupCompleted` - Cleanup operation completed\n511: \n512: ## 11. References\n513: \n514: - [client-go library](../deployment/client-go.md)\n515: - [AR-005: Sandbox Creation Processor](design.md)\n516: - [Kubernetes Delete Options](https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/generated/kubernetes-api/v1.28/#deleteoptions-v1-meta)\n517: - [Finalizers Documentation](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/overview/working-with-objects/finalizers/)\n\n(End of file - total 517 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-006: Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 (Sandbox Deletion and Lifecycle Management)\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-006\n- **Module**: pkg/workloadmanager\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Overview\n\nThe Sandbox Lifecycle Management feature extends the WorkloadManager module to provide comprehensive deletion and lifecycle management for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources. This includes graceful termination, finalizer-based cleanup, deletion callbacks, and lifecycle hooks.\n\n### 1.2 Component Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── client.go              # Kubernetes client initialization (existing)\n├── service.go             # WorkloadManager interface (existing)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md","time":{"start":1775846140073,"end":1775846140089}}}}
